

Install and manage K8s application using Helm

Helm has 2 Components :
Tiller : 
  is the in-cluster component of Helm. It interacts directly with the Kubernetes API server to 
    install, 
    upgrade, 
    query, and 
    remove Kubernetes resources. 
It also stores the objects that represent releases.

Helm client:
  stores information in a local directory is in the $HOME/.helm directory.
  
Charts: Information to create K8s resources in the cluster
  Charts contain a Chart.yaml file as well as templates, default values (values.yaml), and dependencies.
